title: To Kill a Mockingbird
author: Harper Lee
reviewText: A timeless classic that delves into themes of justice and morality. Absolutely loved it!

author: George Orwell
reviewText: A chilling and thought-provoking look into a dystopian future. A must-read for everyone.

title: The Great Gatsby
author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
reviewText: Beautifully written but the story felt a bit slow for me. Still worth a read for the prose.

title: Pride and Prejudice
author: Jane Austen
reviewText: A delightful exploration of relationships and societal norms. Elizabeth Bennet is such a compelling character!

title: The Hobbit
author: J.R.R. Tolkien
reviewText: An engaging adventure with rich storytelling. A fantastic precursor to the Lord of the Rings series.
